get.description:
Use '*' as objectid to determine site-wide permissions.
Default operation is 'view' when 'operation' query param is not provided.
The accepted operation formats are:
  - {application}.{objectType}.{operationCategory}.{operationName}
  - {objectType}.{operationCategory}.{operationName}
  - {operationCategory}.{operationName}
  - {operationName}

When 'objectType' is not provided, it will be derived from the given object id. For example: if 'objectid' is 'artf1234' and operation parameter is 'view.view', then the operation is 'Tracker.Artifact.view.view'.

When only 'operationName' is provided as operation query param, then it will be assumed that 'operationCategory' is same as 'operationName'.
'view' -> 'view.view'.

Examples:
  - '/objects/*/permissions?operation=User.create.create'
  - '/objects/proj1234/permissions?operation=admin'
  - '/objects/proj1234/permissions?operation=Artifact.edit.edit,Tracker.create.createArtifact'
  - '/objects/tracker1234/permissions?operation=Artifact.edit.edit,create.createArtifact'
  - '/objects/artf1234,artf5678/permissions?operation=view,edit,delete'

The response is a map of operation to map of object to boolean. For example:
the response for '/objects/tracker1234,tracker5678/permissions?operation=Artifact.edit.edit,create.createArtifact' is:

<pre>{
  "Artifact.edit.edit": {
    "tracker1234": true,
    "tracker5678": false,
  },
  "create.createArtifact": {
    "tracker1234": true,
    "tracker5678": false,
  }
}
</pre>

<div><b>Since:</b><br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20.3</div><br>
